    A[High Populism Score] -- r=0.73 --> B[High Nationalism Score]
    style A fill:#ffcdd2
    style B fill:#ffcdd2
```

This strong coupling suggests the emergence of a dominant **Ethno-Populist** discourse. Evidence demonstrates how these themes are fused. For example, President Trump's promise to "bring back our jobs" (economic populism) is immediately followed by "bring back our borders" (nationalism) [4]. Similarly, framing concern for "America's forgotten communities" aligns a populist target group with a nationalist in-group [5]. Party platforms also codify this fusion, linking the needs of "American Workers" directly to a nationalist economic policy of returning "Manufacturing Jobs" [6].

